  "explanation": "In determining the sentence, the court considered the defendant's status as a first-time offender and the partial restitution of the $25,000 as significant mitigating factors. However, embezzlement represents a serious breach of fiduciary duty and trust. While the spectator's emotional outburst was entirely disregarded, the nature of the crime warrants more than just probation to serve as a deterrent. A sentence of 6 months reflects the gravity of the financial theft while accounting for the defendant's clean record and efforts to repay the debt.",
